    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-01-25T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-01-25T19:00:00-05:00" n="216"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d216">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.114 St. Pierre-Miquelon/443: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bullitt</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-01-25T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >January 25, 1937—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>37. Your No. 1275, December 18, 3 p.m.<note n="30" xml:id="d216fn30">
                        <ref target="frus1936v01#pg_436">
                            <hi rend="italic">ibid.</hi>, p. 436</ref>.</note> Treasury Department
                    believes it would be mutually helpful if it could receive an outline of proposed
                    decree to replace one now in effect at St. Pierre-Miquelon before it is finally
                    adopted. Please endeavor to obtain and telegraph desired information if you can
                    properly do so.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
